Madl, Hungarian Post-Communist President and Lawyer, Dies at 80

-- B y   Z o l t a n   S i m o n
-- 
2011-05-30T06:10:14Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-30/madl-hungarian-post-communist-president-and-lawyer-dies-at-80.html
Ferenc Madl,  Hungary ’s president
between 2000 and 2005 who led the country into the European
Union, has died. He was 80.  Madl died yesterday, the office of the Hungarian presidency
said on its  website  today. Madl, a lawyer by profession, also
served as a minister in Hungary’s first post-communist Cabinet
in 1990. No details about his death or funeral arrangements were
given.  To contact the reporter responsible for this story:
Zoltan Simon at 
